		"description": "<p>This crossbow has a large winding wheel affixed to its drawstring which feeds into extra machinery along the stock that catches and pulls the string back again after it is fired. </p><p>Winding a ratcheting crossbow for a single bolt requires a bonus action or action, and it can be wound to prepare two bolts. Masterwork ratcheting crossbows can be prepared to fire up to four bolts, or be constructed smaller (with statistics like a hand crossbow).</p><p>When you roll a natural 20 on an attack roll using this weapon it deals an extra 2d6 damage of the weapon's type (this extra damage does not double).</p>",
